WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:13.280 --> 00:00:14.760
Hi. Welcome, everyone.

00:00:14.760 --> 00:00:16.160
My name is Alda Migoni.

00:00:16.160 --> 00:00:18.730
And I'm President of the
Hispanic Cultural Society here

00:00:18.730 --> 00:00:20.030
at the Library of Congress.

00:00:20.030 --> 00:00:22.430
I work as a librarian of
the South American section

00:00:22.430 --> 00:00:25.200
of the African, Latin, American,
and Western European division.

00:00:25.200 --> 00:00:28.320
On behalf of the Hispanic
Cultural Society of the Library

00:00:28.320 --> 00:00:30.110
of Congress, I would
like to welcome you all

00:00:30.110 --> 00:00:31.950
to this featured event in honor

00:00:31.950 --> 00:00:34.730
of National Hispanic
Heritage Month.

00:00:34.730 --> 00:00:37.320
National Hispanic Heritage
Month is celebrated each year

00:00:37.320 --> 00:00:40.090
from September 15
through October 15.

00:00:40.090 --> 00:00:42.030
Enacted into law in 1988,

00:00:42.030 --> 00:00:44.570
this month recognizes the
contributions of Latino

00:00:44.570 --> 00:00:47.090
and Hispanic Americans
in the United States

00:00:47.090 --> 00:00:50.470
and their heritages, cultures,
and many achievements.

00:00:50.470 --> 00:00:53.100
September 15 was chosen to
start the month of celebration

00:00:53.100 --> 00:00:54.770
as it coincides with
the anniversary

00:00:54.770 --> 00:00:57.190
of five Latin Americans
country's independence days.

00:00:57.190 --> 00:01:01.540
September 16, 18, and 21 also
mark the independence of Mexico,

00:01:01.540 --> 00:01:04.630
Chile, and Belize respectively.

00:01:04.630 --> 00:01:06.030
Today we have the
honor of having

00:01:06.030 --> 00:01:09.770
with us Representative
Pete Aguilar

00:01:09.770 --> 00:01:11.890
in a moderated conversation
with law librarian

00:01:11.890 --> 00:01:13.820
of Congress Jane Sanchez.

00:01:13.820 --> 00:01:18.650
So Jane Sanchez is the 25th
law librarian of Congress.

00:01:18.650 --> 00:01:21.040
She manages the operation
and policy administration

00:01:21.040 --> 00:01:23.450
of the law library, the
world's largest collection

00:01:23.450 --> 00:01:24.870
of legal material.

00:01:24.870 --> 00:01:29.240
She assumed the position of law
librarian on February 6, 2017.

00:01:29.240 --> 00:01:31.530
Prior to the law library,
Sanchez had been Chief

00:01:31.530 --> 00:01:33.080
of Humanities and
Social Sciences

00:01:33.080 --> 00:01:36.020
at the Library since
October 2014.

00:01:36.020 --> 00:01:37.610
The division provides
research service

00:01:37.610 --> 00:01:39.940
in the library's main reading
room, its local history

00:01:39.940 --> 00:01:42.860
and genealogy section, its
digital reference team,

00:01:42.860 --> 00:01:45.760
and its microfilm and
electronic resources center.

00:01:45.760 --> 00:01:48.320
Under her leadership, services
to researchers expanded

00:01:48.320 --> 00:01:51.030
and outreach through
the divisions, RSS feed,

00:01:51.030 --> 00:01:54.890
has led to more robust use of
the collections and services.

00:01:54.890 --> 00:01:57.460
She's also served as a
business unit managing director

00:01:57.460 --> 00:01:59.560
at the U.S. Government
Publishing Office,

00:01:59.560 --> 00:02:01.750
as an associate director
of Justice Libraries,

00:02:01.750 --> 00:02:04.400
Justice Management Division,
U.S. Department of Justice,

00:02:04.400 --> 00:02:07.500
as departmental head of
History and Cultural Literatures

00:02:07.500 --> 00:02:09.710
at the Smithsonian
Institution Libraries,

00:02:09.710 --> 00:02:12.970
and as an acquisitions manager
for electronic database at BNA,

00:02:12.970 --> 00:02:16.380
Inc, a legal publisher, in
addition to library work

00:02:16.380 --> 00:02:19.040
at Harvard and the
University of New Mexico.

00:02:19.040 --> 00:02:21.480
She has received numerous awards
over the course of her career,

00:02:21.480 --> 00:02:23.100
including from the U.S.
Department of Energy

00:02:23.100 --> 00:02:24.400
for sustained superior service

00:02:24.400 --> 00:02:26.330
and from the Justice
Management Division

00:02:26.330 --> 00:02:29.990
and the Smithsonian Institution
for Workflow Improvements.

00:02:29.990 --> 00:02:33.460
So Representative Pete
Aguilar represents the 31st

00:02:33.460 --> 00:02:35.410
Congressional District
of California.

00:02:35.410 --> 00:02:37.850
He was first elected
in 2014 and serves

00:02:37.850 --> 00:02:41.180
on the House Appropriations
Committee in the 115th Congress.

00:02:41.180 --> 00:02:43.190
He holds the leadership
positions of Whip,

00:02:43.190 --> 00:02:45.660
of the Congressional Hispanic
Caucus, and is an assistant whip

00:02:45.660 --> 00:02:48.000
in the House Democratic Caucus.

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:49.590
Representative Aguilar
is a voice

00:02:49.590 --> 00:02:53.360
for middle-class families
throughout San Bernardino County

00:02:53.360 --> 00:02:57.070
and prioritizes legislation that
will nurture more fair economy,

00:02:57.070 --> 00:02:59.730
where everyone has
opportunities to succeed.

00:02:59.730 --> 00:03:01.650
He is committed to
policies that create jobs,

00:03:01.650 --> 00:03:04.830
reform our broken immigration
system, supports our students,

00:03:04.830 --> 00:03:07.680
and safeguards vital programs
for seniors and veterans.

00:03:07.680 --> 00:03:08.980
He resides in Redlands,

00:03:08.980 --> 00:03:12.510
California with his wife
Alisha and their two sons.

00:03:12.510 --> 00:03:16.020
So as a fellow Bulldog and the
University of Redland's alumni,

00:03:16.020 --> 00:03:19.420
I'm really excited and happy
that you are here to join us.

00:03:19.420 --> 00:03:21.010
And the Library of Congress

00:03:21.010 --> 00:03:23.670
and Hispanic Cultural
Society welcomes you both.

00:03:23.670 --> 00:03:25.110
So thank you, so much.

00:03:25.110 --> 00:03:27.090
After the moderator
conversation,

00:03:27.090 --> 00:03:29.370
we will open the floor up to
questions from the audience,

00:03:29.370 --> 00:03:33.000
so please, stay tuned for
that and also you are welcome

00:03:33.000 --> 00:03:35.240
for coffee and a
quick chat after.

00:03:35.240 --> 00:03:37.040
Thank you.

